    excerpt: "Built-in premium tier (Sub-Zero, Wolf integrated) vs free-standing flexibility + replacement ease. Service access patterns, cabinetry constraints, honest economics.",
    category: "Repair Tips",
    date: "2026-05-05",
    readingTime: "6 min read",
  },
  {
    slug: "wolf-range-failures-honest-costs",
    title: "Common Wolf Range Failures and Honest Repair Costs",
    excerpt: "Premium tier brand depth: igniter, valve, infrared broiler patterns. Wolf vs Sub-Zero coordination (same parent company). BH/WeHo/Beverly Hills service patterns.",
    category: "Brand-Specific",
    date: "2026-05-05",
    readingTime: "7 min read",
  },
  // Wave 27a — final 7 articles to reach 20-article master plan target
  {
    slug: "lg-vs-samsung-washer-which-breaks-down-less",
    title: "LG vs Samsung Washer: Which Breaks Down Less in LA",
    excerpt: "Direct-drive vs belt-driven motor architecture, year-pattern failure data, LA hard water impact. Honest middle-ground recommendation from a tech who services both brands daily.",
    category: "Brand-Specific",
    date: "2026-05-05",
    readingTime: "8 min read",
  },
  {
    slug: "why-refrigerator-is-loud-7-causes",
    title: "Why Your Refrigerator Is Loud: 7 Causes Ranked by Likelihood",
